        "### Worked example 11.7: four critical points\n",
        "\n",
        "Let\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "f(x,y)=x^3+y^3+3x^2-3y^2-7.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "The first derivatives are\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "f_x=3x^2+6x=3x(x+2),\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "and\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "f_y=3y^2-6y=3y(y-2).\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Therefore\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "x=0\\text{ or }x=-2,\n",
        "\\qquad\n",
        " y=0\\text{ or }y=2.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "The critical points are\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "(0,0),\\quad (0,2),\\quad (-2,0),\\quad (-2,2).\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "The second derivatives are\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "f_{xx}=6x+6,\n",
        "\\qquad\n",
        "f_{yy}=6y-6,\n",
        "\\qquad\n",
        "f_{xy}=0.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Since $D=f_{xx}f_{yy}$:\n",
        "\n",
        "- at $(0,0)$, $D=6(-6)<0$, so it is a saddle point;\n",
        "- at $(0,2)$, $D=6(6)>0$ and $f_{xx}>0$, so it is a local minimum;\n",
        "- at $(-2,0)$, $D=(-6)(-6)>0$ and $f_{xx}<0$, so it is a local maximum;\n",
        "- at $(-2,2)$, $D=(-6)(6)<0$, so it is a saddle point.\n",
        "\n",
        "## 11.6 Absolute extrema on closed bounded regions\n",
        "\n",
        "Local extrema describe what happens near a point. Absolute extrema describe the largest and smallest values on an entire region.\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.callout-note}\n",
        "## Extreme value principle\n",
        "\n",
        "If $f$ is continuous on a closed and bounded region $D\\subset \\mathbb R^2$, then $f$ attains both an absolute maximum and an absolute minimum on $D$.\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "To find absolute extrema on a closed bounded region:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. find critical points inside $D$;\n",
        "2. find extrema on the boundary of $D$;\n",
        "3. compare all candidate values.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Worked example 11.8: extrema on a rectangle\n",
        "\n",
        "Find the absolute maximum and minimum of\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "f(x,y)=x^2-2xy+2y\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "on the rectangle\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "D=\\{(x,y):0\\leq x\\leq 3,\\;0\\leq y\\leq 2\\}.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Interior critical points satisfy\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "f_x=2x-2y=0,\n",
        "\\qquad\n",
        "f_y=-2x+2=0.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "So $x=1$ and $y=1$. The interior value is\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "f(1,1)=1.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Now check the four boundary sides.\n",
        "\n",
        "On $x=0$:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "f(0,y)=2y,\n",
        "\\qquad 0\\leq y\\leq 2,\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "so the boundary values range from $0$ to $4$.\n",
        "\n",
        "On $x=3$:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "f(3,y)=9-4y,\n",
        "\\qquad 0\\leq y\\leq 2,\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "so the boundary values range from $1$ to $9$.\n",
        "\n",
        "On $y=0$:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
